Our show today continues the discussion with Philip Jose Farmer.

18:05.160 --> 18:11.120
A major incident in Farmer's career began when Venus on the Half Shell, a novel written under the pseudonym Kilgore Trout,

18:11.520 --> 18:15.680
appeared in the pages of fantasy and science fiction in late 74, early 75.

18:16.280 --> 18:19.220
Of course, Kilgore Trout is the creation of author Kurt Vonnegut Jr.

18:19.840 --> 18:25.380
The character Trout is an impoverished, underappreciated science fiction writer who appears in a number of Vonnegut's novels.

18:25.380 --> 18:28.360
We asked Farmer if he identifies with Kilgore Trout.

18:55.520 --> 19:00.480
We're being taken due to our inexperience with various publishers and agents.

19:02.500 --> 19:04.840
Also, I had a tough time getting any recognition.

19:06.480 --> 19:09.100
So I guess that's why I identified with him.

19:09.540 --> 19:10.840
Most of the fact is he's a great character.

19:12.360 --> 19:17.180
Vonnegut did not appreciate the reviews given Venus on the Half Shell, either pro or con,

19:17.360 --> 19:20.840
because most of the reviewers approached the work as if Vonnegut were the author.

19:20.840 --> 19:25.560
This cost Farmer the opportunity to write another novel under the Kilgore Trout pseudonym.

19:51.100 --> 19:56.420
When I applied for permission to write The Son of Jimmy Valentine, which I really would have loved to,

19:56.660 --> 20:03.000
I could have had a lot of fun with it, he said no, which is his prerogative.

20:04.760 --> 20:08.660
We asked if The Son of Jimmy Valentine was Kilgore Trout's one erotic novel.

20:10.140 --> 20:18.220
It was not only his one and only specifically erotic book, it was also his only non-science fiction book.

20:19.220 --> 20:25.320
Farmer obviously enjoys writing about fictional authors who in turn write about their own fictional authors and so on.

20:25.720 --> 20:28.660
Listen as he describes what writing as Kilgore Trout started.

20:29.500 --> 20:38.100
In the Venus on the Half Shell, the protagonist, Simon Lagstaff, had his favorite science fiction author.

20:38.900 --> 20:45.000
Just as in Vonnegut's books, Elliott Rose Water lost the Kilgore Trout,

20:45.100 --> 20:48.520
the greatest living writer in any field.

20:48.620 --> 20:51.120
He should have been president of the US, he couldn't have solved all the problems.

20:51.940 --> 21:02.280
Well anyway, in Venus on the Half Shell, Simon Lagstaff liked to read the science fiction works of a fellow called Jonathan Swiss Summers the Third.

21:03.060 --> 21:08.380
And I describe his various works as a Ralf item and give the titles.

21:09.640 --> 21:23.460
But Jonathan Swiss Summers, who's a fictional author, wrote about a giant German shepherd police dog whose IQ had been raised to about 200 in a laboratory and he became a private detective.

21:24.580 --> 21:34.900
Now, I plan eventually on writing a book by Ralf von Baubau, this dog, under the name Ralf von Baubau.

21:36.520 --> 21:48.760
And then maybe I'll end the cycle by having Ralf von Baubau write about a human named Vonnegut or something like that and completing it, going right back to Vonnegut again.

21:49.900 --> 21:58.020
Farmer conceded with the extended family group called the Vold Newton family in which many great historical and fictional characters are descended from the scarlet Pimpernel.

21:58.680 --> 22:04.620
Thus Kilgore Trout is related to Sherlock Holmes, Doc Savage, Sam Spade and James Bond among others.

22:05.260 --> 22:08.180
We will look into this aspect of Farmer's writing some more tomorrow.

